= Introduction

This is the introduction. Replace this placeholder text with your own, but keep
the structure as a guide: open with the broad context, narrow to the specific
problem your thesis addresses, and end with a clear statement of your aims. The
paragraphs below exist only to show how body text, citations, cross-references,
and block quotes render in this template.

The introduction sets the scene and motivates the work. State what is known,
cite the sources that establish it @smith2020 @jones2019, and then identify the
gap that your thesis fills. Citations use the author–year (APA) style and are
rendered in black, like the surrounding text, so the printed page stays clean;
they remain clickable in the PDF. A single citation looks like this
@garcia2021, and a parenthetical group looks like this
@smith2020 @mueller2018.

== Background

Use level-two headings for the main sections within a chapter, and level-three
headings for subsections beneath them. Every heading is numbered automatically
(you can turn numbering off with `heading-numbering: false` in `main.typ`) and
appears in the table of contents.

Body paragraphs are justified with a comfortable line height. Emphasis comes in
two forms: *bold* for strong emphasis and _italic_ for terms and titles. Inline
code, such as a variable name like `threshold` or a short command, is set in a
lightly shaded box.

== Aims and objectives

State the central aim of the thesis plainly. It often helps to isolate the core
hypothesis or research question as a block quote, which this template renders
with a left rule in italic:

#quote(block: true)[
  The central hypothesis of this thesis is that a clearly stated research
  question, set apart from the surrounding text, is easier for a reader (and an
  examiner) to find and to hold in mind.
]

From that aim, derive a short list of concrete objectives:

+ Establish the problem and review the relevant literature.
+ Describe the data and the method used to address the problem.
+ Present the results and interpret them.
+ Discuss the implications, limitations, and possible extensions.

== Thesis structure

Close the introduction with a brief road map. The Methodology chapter describes
the materials and procedure (and shows how figures and tables look — see
@fig:method-overview and @tab:parameters). The Results chapter reports the
findings, and the Discussion chapter interprets them and concludes.
